In the Matter of Eunice Conroy CARON, Bankrupt. Eunice Conroy CARON v. Arthur G. WOLFF, Trustee, etc. No. 6370. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Oct. 21, 1937. John M. Redford, of Milwaukee, Wis., for appellant. Gold & McCann, of Milwaukee, Wis., for appellee.

Before EVANS, SPARKS, and MAJOR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
